                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>A multicoloured leather binding with gilded medallions and ornations. The
                        spine was a later addition during a restoration in the 19th Century. The
                        binding was restored in 1999-2002, when the codex underwent a throrough
                        restoration and conservation in Cambridge University Library's Conservation
                        Department by Kristine Rose and Deborah Farndell.</p>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <p>The drop-shaped <locus from="1r" to="1r">Golkonda seal</locus> on the first
                        page appears to be that of Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah, Sultan of Golkunda,
                        1565-1612 with the date 1012 [1603/4 C.E.] and a later inscription dated
                           <date calendar="Hijri-qamari" from="1610" to="1611">1091</date> [1610/11
                        C.E.]</p>
                  </sealDesc>
